<div id="review_2504440783" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2504440783" />
    <a title="Terry" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/68153909-terry"><img alt="Terry" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1618947475p2/68153909.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2504440783?book_show_action=true">Sep 06, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Terry" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Terry" href="/user/show/68153909-terry">Terry</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2504440783" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3829749138131974984">I loved the first Act of this play. I even enjoyed scene 1 of Act II. After that, however, it was all downhill. The end was too fast and too much happening with little development and rushed resolutions to the various stories. The first Act was absolutely great! Great language and flow, character development etc. I don&apos;t understand how the second Act fell apart so much, but, hey, this won the Pulitzer Prize for literature; so, what do I know!? lol</span>
  <span id="freeText3829749138131974984" style="display:none">I loved the first Act of this play. I even enjoyed scene 1 of Act II. After that, however, it was all downhill. The end was too fast and too much happening with little development and rushed resolutions to the various stories. The first Act was absolutely great! Great language and flow, character development etc. I don't understand how the second Act fell apart so much, but, hey, this won the Pulitzer Prize for literature; so, what do I know!? lol</span>
